commit.message:
Updated a few wiki/reference pages with new info, fixed bad links.
Changed GTKDIALOG=gtkdialog in all examples/applications to [ -z  ] && GTKDIALOG=gtkdialog to make it easier to change versions/builds e.g. GTKDIALOG=gtk3dialog ./examples/expander/expander.
Tested all examples up to fontbutton for compatibility with GTK+ 3.
Renamed "column-width" to "column-sizing" -- value >= 2 becomes width.
Tweaked the column-width custom tag attribute to support autoresize.

Renamed the recently added --style-sheet command line option to --styles which requires a gtkrc for gtk2 or a gtk.css for gtk3.
Renamed the loadstylesheet action function to loadstyles as it should work in gtk2 too but I haven't managed to do that yet. gtk3 works now.
Added the "column-width" tag attribute to the tree widget.

gtk3: Added the --style-sheet command line option -- still operational within a GTK+ 2 build but an unsupported warning message is displayed which is preferable to a gtk unknown command line option error.
gtk3: Added the loadstylesheet action function -- still operational within a GTK+ 2 build but an unsupported warning message is displayed.
Added examples/demoscene filled with SFR's awesome demos.

Added gtk3 specific code to the comboboxtext and comboboxentry widgets so that they now function identically to the gtk2 equivalents.
The file selection dialog filename retrieval issue was specific to less than gtk-2.4.0 so I've wrapped it in a macro for those versions.
Added "GTK+ 2/3" to the supported libraries list with gtkdialog -v.
Added the "column-resizeable" tag attribute to the tree widget.
Updated a few wiki/reference pages with new info, fixed bad links.
Added helpful error messages when attempting to create combobox, list and table widgets with GTK+ 3.
Build script update to stop automake 1.13.1 complaining.

Added initial support for GTK+ 3 with the --enable-gtk3=yes configure option; widgets removed: combobox, list, table; require rewriting: comboboxtext, comboboxentry, file selection dialog filename retrieval.
Incremented the version number only.

Version 0.8.3 released (r502)
Finished the Pfeme example application.
pfeme updates: see pfeme ChangeLog.
pfeme updates: see pfeme ChangeLog.
pfeme updates: see pfeme ChangeLog.

pfeme updates: see pfeme ChangeLog.
Reference Docs updates: Gtk+ 2 Reference Docs URL has changed.
pfeme updates: see pfeme ChangeLog.
Corrected to backticks and tested with dash all of the examples. Those that require bash also use bash where necessary within actions.
Corrected to backticks and tested with dash all examples up to playmusic (so far show_and_hide progressbar with dash is unstable\!).
Corrected to backticks and tested with dash all examples up to miscellaneous.
Corrected to backticks and tested with dash all examples up to menuitemseparator.
Added the GtkMenuShell to the widget visibility list which I missed. This is the pop-up rectangle that contains the menuitems.

Added support for break i.e. don't process any more actions.
Added examples/miscellaneous/break.
Updated the reference docs.

Corrected to backticks and tested with dash all examples up to frame.
Changed index++ in Pfontview and Pfeme because dash didn't like it, and tested to work.

Applied any existing use-markup="true" tag attributes to text widgets on widget creation to prevent visible resizing when being shown.
Started to change all "" to "" within the examples.
Added examples/miscellaneous/conditional_actions.

Fixed bashisms within examples where possible, changed /bin/sh to/bin/bash where it wasn't.
Fixed examples/edit/edit_attributes having duplicate variable names.
Fixed examples/progressbar/progressbar_closewindow not closing.
Fixed progressbar examples echoing data after pipe had closed.

Changed <action type="function"> to <action function="type"> because that's what it should be which is especially obvious now that we have signal="type" and condition="type"; type="function" is now deprecated.
Updated some examples to use the new <action function="type">.
Removed "if " from conditions since we only need the conditions now. 
Updated the reference docs.

Changed "if function(argument)" and "if ! function(argument)" to "if function_is_true(argument)" and "if function_is_false(argument)" because the not symbol will be interpreted as notting. Not only is it now clearer, it was easier to implement and it could be expanded upon.
